title: Ignition, CyBoxes, and Alarm Audio disabled. x2151 forwarded to Ops cell phone. ACR unstaffed.
DAY-SHIFT Report 2022-01-10, Mon
text: DAY-SHIFT Report 2022-01-10, Mon PROGRAM: Accelerator Physics, 500 mA, 300 s top-off injection BEAMLINES: All open FAULTS: 1110 BL10-1 IG5, monitoring BL10-1 MR2 space, reports pressure spike above trip point 1E-07 torr, causing PR2 fault, closing BL10. Upon attending, BL10-1 IG5 display remains dark and does not reset. Sticker on display indicates first filament burned out 2018-01-08. Escalated to vac tech. Vac techs report 2018 sticker is obsolete, second filament is available; and wired in. Cleared fault at BL10-1 rack and BL10-0 rack; and reopened beamline at 1210. Removed obsolete 2018 sticker 1310 BL14-3 He trips low during staff reconfiguration of beamline, sounding building alarm. Silenced alarm, acknowledged fault EXPERIMENTS: 1035 Gas order placed 1650 Assisted experimenters on BL4-1 to locate regulator O rings

This new firmware was uploaded to the VFD back on Friday, 12/17/2021 by MECOS AG. 01/10/22 13:15 - Antonio De Lira - C0 (common) - HRS.UT.EL-Cristian Perinet (F&O HV electrician) has just called to inform Cryoplant operation that the 12 kV busses have been split, i.e. the 12 kV power to the Cryoplant and the SPEAR3 accelerator sit now on separate busses. 01/10/22 12:36 - Randall Chase - C1 - HRS.4K.CB-Found leak at output of C1PSV22195. He background at 7.8 x 10e-6 ATM.cc/sec. Leak rate at 1.2 x 10e-4 ATM.cc/sec. 01/10/22 12:00 - Roland Evans - C1 - HRS.2K.IT-Providing electrical and instrumentation support to Dayne and Antonio on the 2K cold box cold compressor's controls. 01/10/22 11:28 - Dirk Pflueckhahn - C1 - HRS.4K.00-Repressurized phase separator to 1.5 bara for leak check of PSV22195. 01/10/22 11:23 - Dirk Pflueckhahn - C1 - HRS.ST.LH-Closed MV31014 and pressurized 10K Dewar to verify that its tight and PV31020 is NOT leaking into CD line 01/10/22 09:00 - Roland Evans - C0 (common) - HRS.00.00-I did the plant walk through, I found no issues. "01/10/22 08:10 - Vishy Ravindranath - C0 (common) - HRS.AX.EP-With Randall's support Bed1 Vacuum Pump stopped Following Bed1 Pressures were noted: Cold trap to Pump = 0.01 mbar Adsorber Pressure = 0.02 mbar Bed1 back filled = 6.8 bara" "01/10/22 07:00 - Kyle Connally - C0 (common) - HRS.DB.00-HRS.DB.00- Cleaned up area around Downstream DB and moved all tools and parts to the Upstream DB. On the Upstream DB, on the exhaust side (B side), when Greg and I loosened up the bolts of the 6" flange to extract the old burst disc we noticed some water seepage coming from the spiral wound gasket. Thinking it was probably a little condensation we proceeded with jacking up the top flange to get enough room to pull the old burst disk out. When we pulled it out we noticed right away that the burst disk was filled to the brim with water. A plausible reason why this happened could not be decided. Greg and I, after Dirk examined the situation and had vacuumed some debris from inside the line, continued with installing the new burst disc. Everything is torqued down."
